&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;T&amp;O Senior Clinical Fellowship: Trauma (Post FRCS Orth)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;(January &amp; October 2021)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ashford and St. Peter’s Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust would like to invite applications for a Senior Clinical + Research Fellowship post covering Trauma Orthopaedic Surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will commence from 4th January 2021 for a period of 10 months. You are also welcome to apply for October 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is designed for trainees who are ideally post CCT (or within 6/12 of CCT), and have completed FRCS (Orth) exam from a UK / Australian orthopaedic training scheme, or those with equivalent additional clinical experience. The candidate must be capable of independent operating.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Brief Description of Clinical Duties: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have supervised operating lists and will be expected to operate independently. Ideally this post would suit a senior trainee wishing to consolidate their skills before moving onto a consultant position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Smita Shetty – smita.shetty1@nhs.net or 01932 872000 ext 2405&lt;/p&gt;
